# Cross-platform line-ending discipline (Pitfall research §gitattributes recommendation).
#
# Why this file exists: a Windows checkout's default core.autocrlf=true would
# normalize every shell script to CRLF on disk, then on a Linux CI runner the
# CRLF poisons `bash: \r: No such file or directory`. Worse, during the
# monthly upstream-sync (Plan 01-05 / FORK-05), each cross-platform clone
# would produce a different working-tree state and the merge with upstream
# microsoft/vscode would diff against phantom CRLF noise on every shell file.
# Pinning eol=lf in-repo + OS-native on checkout makes the working tree
# deterministic across Linux / macOS / Windows.
#
# Strategy when upstream microsoft/vscode is cloned (Plan 01-03):
#   - If upstream ships its own .gitattributes, prepend this block.
#   - On per-extension conflict, upstream wins (we're a fork, we don't fight
#     upstream's discipline). The exception is shell scripts, which MUST
#     remain LF regardless — upstream's vscode/.gitattributes already enforces
#     `*.sh text eol=lf` so there is no real conflict.

# Default: auto-detect text files, normalize to LF in repo, OS-native on checkout.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Shell scripts MUST be LF (CRLF breaks bash on Linux/Mac runners).
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.bash text eol=lf

# Node ESM / CommonJS scripts MUST be LF.
*.mjs  text eol=lf
*.cjs  text eol=lf
*.js   text eol=lf

# YAML, Markdown, JSON: normalize to LF.
*.yml  text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.md   text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf

# Windows-only batch / cmd scripts: keep CRLF (cmd.exe requires it).
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf

# Binary files: never normalize.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.icns  binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
*.eot   binary

# UPSTREAM_BASE is shell-sourceable (sourced by scripts/upstream-sync.sh):
# must be LF or `bash source` will choke on CRLF on Linux runners.
UPSTREAM_BASE text eol=lf

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Appended from upstream microsoft/vscode .gitattributes (1.117.0).
# Upstream-specific rules that don't conflict with the GoatIDE block above.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Upstream pins these specific files to CRLF (legal text):
LICENSE.txt eol=crlf
ThirdPartyNotices.txt eol=crlf

# Upstream pins PowerShell scripts to LF.
*.ps1 eol=lf

# RTF treated as binary by upstream.
*.rtf -text

# JSON files in upstream are jsonc (with comments) — Linguist hint.
**/*.json linguist-language=jsonc
